query.result:
13 "O my dear little plant, who so absorb yourself, 14 that, just as earthly minds see 15 that two obtuse angles cannot fit into a triangle,
16 so you see contingent things 17 before they are in themselves, by looking at the point 18 at which all times are present;
19 while I was joined to Virgil 20 up on the mountain that heals souls 21 and descending into the defunct world,
22 grave words were spoken to me about my future life, 23 although I feel myself 24 well squared against the blows of fortune;
25 therefore my desire would be content 26 to understand what fortune approaches me: 27 for a foreseen arrow comes more slowly."

